cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with identifying devices from their transmitted signals and offers an additional factor of authentication for preventing impersonation attacks. It could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with identifying devices from their network traffic. The paper also introduces a novel Deep Complex-valued Neural Network (DCN) for modeling raw RF signals, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions open air captures and provides guidelines for future explorations, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
